[size=14pt][b]What is Quillon-NarwhalKnight?[/b][/size]

Quillon-NarwhalKnight is a quantum-enhanced distributed consensus protocol that extends DAG-Knight BFT with:
[list]
[*][b]NIST Level 5 Post-Quantum Cryptography[/b] (Dilithium5 + Kyber1024) - [color=green]✓ Code-Verified[/color]
[*][b]Novel Q-Resonance Consensus Module[/b] - [color=orange]⚠ Testnet, External Audit Q1 2025[/color]
[*][b]Privacy-as-a-Service (PaaS)[/b] - Multi-chain privacy with differential privacy guarantees - [color=green]✓ Testnet Verified[/color]
[/list]

[color=blue][b]Current Status:[/b][/color] [b]Testnet deployment with enterprise pilots (Q4 2025).[/b] Mainnet launch planned Q1 2026 pending external security audits.

[size=14pt][b]What Makes This Different?[/b][/size]

[b]1. Radical Transparency[/b]
We don't hide limitations. Our whitepaper includes a full "Known Limitations and Risks" section (pp. 25-26). Every technical claim is backed by code references or clearly marked as "testnet target" or "in development."

[b]2. Code-Verified Claims[/b]
We provide a complete [url=https://code.quillon.xyz/PAAS_IMPLEMENTATION_VERIFICATION_MATRIX.md]Implementation Verification Matrix[/url] mapping each whitepaper claim to actual code with line numbers. No vaporware.

[b]3. Measured Performance (October 2025 Testnet)[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Standard Transactions:[/b] 1,030 TPS measured (200 concurrent clients, 100% success rate)
[*][b]PaaS API Operations:[/b] 970 TPS for key generation (testnet verified)
[*][b]Latency P50/P99:[/b] 32ms / 393ms for standard transactions
[*][b]Consensus Finality:[/b] ~2.9 seconds (testnet average)
[*][color=red][b]Important:[/b][/color] These are optimal testnet conditions. Real-world mainnet performance will vary based on network conditions, geographic distribution, and load patterns. Privacy mixing features currently in active development.
[/list]

