[size=10pt][i](Full disclosure - see whitepaper pp. 25-26)[/i][/size]

[b]Deployment Status:[/b]
[list]
[*]Currently testnet-only (NOT mainnet)
[*]Mainnet launch Q1 2026 pending audits
[*]Enterprise pilots active with select partners (Q4 2025)
[/list]

[b]Performance Limitations:[/b]
[list]
[*]Testnet benchmarks: 1,030 TPS measured under optimal conditions with 200 concurrent clients
[*]Real-world mainnet performance expected lower due to geographic distribution and network latency
[*]Post-quantum signatures are 40x larger than ECDSA (bandwidth overhead)
[*]ZK-STARK proofs are 10-100 KB (vs 200 bytes for SNARKs)
[*]Privacy mixing currently in development (not production-ready)
[/list]

[b]Multi-Chain Support:[/b]
[list]
[*]Current (Q4 2025): Bitcoin + Ethereum + EVM chains
[*]Q2 2026: Solana integration planned
[*]Future: Other chains TBD based on community demand
[/list]

[b]Regulatory Risks:[/b]
[list]
[*]Tornado Cash precedent shows privacy tools face regulatory scrutiny
[*]Service may be restricted in some jurisdictions
[*]Users responsible for compliance with local laws
